Write a java program to sort characters in String in java?
:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
Step1.Taking one String as a Input.
Step2.Convert String to Character Array.
Step3.Sorting character in array using Arrays.sort() method.
Step4.Construct String using Sorted Character Array.

:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
package io.javabrains;

import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.Scanner;

public class StringSorting {
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		System.out.println("Enter Input String:- ");
		Scanner scan = new Scanner(System.in);
		String inputString = scan.nextLine();

		char[] ch = inputString.toCharArray();
		Arrays.sort(ch);

		String sortedString = new String(ch);
		System.out.println(ch);

	}
}
